define({"topics" : [{"title":"Generate lists (gen-list)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">gen-list</code> step examines the input files and creates lists of topics, images, document     properties, or other content. These lists are used by later steps in the pipeline. This step is implemented in     Java.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-genlist.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-genlist",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-genlist-d50e3041","topics":[]},{"title":"Debug and filter (debug-filter)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">debug-filter</code> step processes all referenced DITA content and creates copies in a     temporary directory. As the DITA content is copied, filtering is performed, debugging information is inserted, and     table column names are adjusted. This step is implemented in Java.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-debugfilter.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-debugfilter",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-debugfilter-d50e3065","topics":[]},{"title":"Resolve map references (mapref)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">mapref</code> step resolves references from one DITA map to another. This step is implemented     in XSLT.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-mapref.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-mapref",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-mapref-d50e3089","topics":[]},{"title":"Branch filtering (branch-filter)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">branch-filter</code> step filters topics using DITAVAL files defined in the map.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-branch-filter.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-branch-filter",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-branch-filter-d50e3113","topics":[]},{"title":"Copy related files (copy-files)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">copy-files</code> step copies non-DITA resources to the output directory, such as HTML files     that are referenced in a map or images that are referenced by a DITAVAL file. Which files are copied depends on the     transformation type.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-copyfiles.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-copyfiles",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-copyfiles-d50e3137","topics":[]},{"title":"Resolve key references (keyref)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">keyref</code> step examines all the keys that are defined in the DITA source and resolves the     key references. Links that make use of keys are updated so that any <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlatt\">@href </code>value is replaced by the     appropriate target; key-based text replacement is also performed, and the key definition list file is written to the     temporary directory. This step is implemented in Java.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-keyref.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-keyref",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-keyref-d50e3161","topics":[]},{"title":"Copy topics (copy-to)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">copy-to</code> step makes a copy of original topic resources to new resources defined by the       <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlatt\">@copy-to</code> attribute.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-copy-to.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-copy-to",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-copy-to-d50e3188","topics":[]},{"title":"Conref push (conrefpush)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">conrefpush</code> step resolves \"conref push\" references. This step only processes documents     that use conref push or that are updated due to the push action. This step is implemented in Java.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-conrefpush.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-conrefpush",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-conrefpush-d50e3215","topics":[]},{"title":"Resolve content references (conref)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">conref</code> step resolves content references, processing only the DITA maps or topics that     use the <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlatt\">@conref</code> attribute. This step is implemented in XSLT.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-conref.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-conref",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-conref-d50e3239","topics":[]},{"title":"Filter conditional content (profile)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">profile</code> step removes content from topics and maps based on the rules in DITAVAL files     or the <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlatt\">@print</code> attribute setting. Output can differ based on when filtering is done.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-profile.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-profile",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-profile-d50e3266","topics":[]},{"title":"Resolve topic fragments and code references (topic-fragment)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">topic-fragment</code> step expands content references to elements in the same topic and     resolves references made with the <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlelement\">&lt;coderef&gt;</code> element. This step is implemented in SAX     pipes.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-topic-fragment.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-topic-fragment",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-topic-fragment-d50e3294","topics":[]},{"title":"Chunk topics (chunk)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">chunk</code> step breaks apart and assembles referenced DITA content based on the @chunk     attribute in maps. This step is implemented in Java.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-chunk.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-chunk",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-chunk-d50e3321","topics":[]},{"title":"Move metadata (move-meta-entries) and pull content into maps (mappull) ","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">move-meta-entries</code> step pushes metadata back and forth between maps and topics. For     example, index entries and copyrights in the map are pushed into affected topics, so that the topics can be     processed later in isolation while retaining all relevant metadata. This step is implemented in Java.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-metadata.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-metadata",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-metadata-d50e3345","topics":[]},{"title":"Map based linking (maplink)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">This step collects links based on a map and moves those links into the referenced topics. The links are     created based on hierarchy in the DITA map, the <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlatt\">@collection-type</code> attribute, and relationship tables.     This step is implemented in XSLT and Java.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-maplink.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-maplink",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-maplink-d50e3369","topics":[]},{"title":"Pull content into topics (topicpull)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">topicpull</code> step pulls content into <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlelement\">&lt;xref&gt;</code> and       <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlelement\">&lt;link&gt;</code> elements. This step is implemented in XSLT.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-topicpull.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-topicpull",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-topicpull-d50e3393","topics":[]},{"title":"Flagging (flag-module)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Beginning with DITA-OT 1.7, flagging support is implemented as a common <code class=\"ph codeph\">flag-module</code>     preprocessing step. The module evaluates the DITAVAL against all flagging attributes, and adds DITA-OTâ€“specific     hints to the topic when flags are active. Any extended transformation type may use these hints to support flagging     without adding logic to interpret the DITAVAL.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-flagging.html","attributes": {"data-id":"flagging",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"flagging-d50e3423","topics":[]},{"title":"Map cleanup (clean-map)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">clean-map</code> step removes any elements and attributes that were added to files to support     preprocessing.</p>","href":"reference\/preprocess-clean-map.html","attributes": {"data-id":"preprocess-clean-map",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"preprocess-clean-map-d50e3447","topics":[]}]});